web_snippets: Elected in 2010 as Utah's 16th Senator, Mike Lee has spent his career defending the fundamental liberties of all Americans.
Mike Lee (born June 4, 1971, Mesa, Arizona, US) is an American politician who was elected as a Republican to the US Senate in 2010.
Mike Lee is co-founder of MyFitnessPal, the world's leading health and fitness platform. Prior to founding MyFitnessPal, Mike co-founded NextC.
